Round 1:
[Patient] "What foods can help me manage my heart failure?"
[Educator] "Try to eat more fruits, vegetables, and whole grains for a healthy heart."

Round 2:
[Patient] "Are there any specific foods I should avoid?"
[Educator] "Limit your intake of salty and processed foods to help your heart stay strong."

Round 3:
[Patient] "Can I still enjoy my favorite soul food dishes?"
[Educator] "You can still enjoy soul food, just try to make healthier versions with less salt and fat."

Round 4:
[Patient] "What about drinks, can I still have my sweet tea?"
[Educator] "Try to limit sugary drinks like sweet tea, and opt for water or unsweetened beverages."

Round 5:
[Patient] "Any tips for cooking heart-healthy meals at home?"
[Educator] "Cook with less oil and salt, and use herbs and spices for flavor instead."